race.comment: A tough race to round out the program. SOMETHING FORJO (8) dropped out from the rails draw before closing late beaten 3L over 1500m at Warwick. Brought solid Toowoomba form to that and they have all been in stronger than this. Can sit handier and she's well placed to win this contest. NEOCLASSICISM (7) resumed over 1203m at Murwillumbah and impressed when beaten from the back by 1.4L - and with a slipped saddle in the straight. He has won on this surface and the extra distance suits. Will need a good ride but can feature with average luck. TAKUNAI (4) has been caught wide his last two but was good over this distance at Warwick prior. Has a handy 1.5kg claim and the inside barrier is a positive. We can see a lot more from him. THE WELLIAN (5) has a cruel barrier but has more to give third-up. Races well here, and the 3kg claim brings him into it. AIMA SUN (11) is hard to catch but has pieces of form that would see her competitive.
